The lion has always symbolized nobility and strength.  Like all large cats, he is a fascinating creature, sinuously graceful, agile and powerful.  Lions show no mercy toward their prey, but care much for their cubs.  Over the centuries fables and stories have consolidated the lion's legend.  Lions stalked through Europe in prehistoric times, and the cave lion was a probable contemporary of Neanderthal and Cro-Magnon man, who hunted-and feared- the great cats over the millennia.  In more recent times, the relationship between man and the lion has changed, with man becoming the predator and the lion the prey.  Today free-ranging lion populations can be found only in the wildlife parks and sanctuaries of Eastern Africa.
